race.comment: THE GRUMPY BEAR (5) ran on hard to just miss fresh then was sent out favourite last time but bombed the start. Well placed here and worth another chance. LEGACY BEL (12) finished runner-up two on end then broke through for a deserved win last time to land the maiden win. In form and expected to give a sight again. FLYING JUDE (9) was a determined winner fresh racing on speed then well off best over further last time. Back in trip and grade and has upside. Gets chance to atone.  MISSION GOLD (6) is a consistent type much improved by two runs back from a break. Last start scored by half a length over 1000m at Mildura. Has upside and can measure up again.
race.rail_position: +4m from the 400m to the winning post, True Remainder. (Pent: 5.60)
